{{Infobox football league season | competition = [[Eredivisie|Netherl. Football Championship]] | season = 1894-95 | winners = [[Koninklijke HFC]] (3rd title) | prevseason = [[1893–94 Netherlands Football League Championship|1893–94]] | nextseason = [[1895–96 Netherlands Football League Championship|1895–96]] }}
The '''[[Eredivisie|Netherlands Football League Championship]] 1894/1895''' was contested by six teams from the cities [[Amsterdam]], [[The Hague]], [[Haarlem]], [[Rotterdam]] and [[Wageningen]]. The teams participated in the competition that would later be called ''Eerste Klasse West''. But since the western football district of the Netherlands was the only one to have a competition at the time, it could be regarded as a national championship. This was also the reason that [[GVC (football club)|Go Ahead Wageningen]] participated, as they would later play in the eastern division. [[Koninklijke HFC]] won the championship.
==New entrant== * [[Rapiditas Rotterdam]]
