'''Alexandru Bratan''' (born 23 August 1977 in [[Cahul]]) is a male [[weightlifter]] from [[Moldova]]. He twice competed for his native [[Eastern Europe]]an country at the [[Summer Olympics]]: 2000 and 2004. He is best known for winning the silver medal in the men's heavyweight division (&ndash; 105&nbsp;kg) at the [[2005 World Weightlifting Championships]]. His brother is [[Eugen Bratan]].

In 2006 the [[International Weightlifting Federation]] (IWF) banned Alexandru Bratan for life, for the second doping violation.<ref>[http://www.rfi.ro/sport-70175-actualitatea-sportiv-22-august-2013 Actualitatea sportivă 22 august 2013]. Christian Frisk, rfi.ro {{ro icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www.iwf.net/anti-doping/sanctions/ Sanctioned Athletes / Athlete Support Personnel]. iwf.net</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timpul.md/articol/(ruine)-halterofilul-igor-bour-a-fost-suspendat-pe-viaa-din-sport-47461.html|title=(RUȘINE) Halterofilul Igor Bour a fost SUSPENDAT pe VIAȚĂ din sport|publisher=timpul.md|accessdate=6 April 2017|language=ro}}</ref>

