'''Birama Gaye''' (born 1964) is a Mauritanian [[Association football|football]] manager.

Gaye has managed Mauritanean clubs [[ASC Nasr de Sebkha]]<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Panafrican News Agency|title=Birama Gaye resigns as Nasr coach|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-100180899/birama-gaye-resigns-nasr.html|date=9 April 2003}}</ref> and [[ASC Tevragh-Zeïne]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Magharebia|title=Tunisian clubs progress in CAF contests|url=http://magharebia.com/cocoon/awi/xhtml1/en_GB/features/awi/articles/2011/04/04/feature-07|date=4 April 2011}}</ref>

He has managed the [[Mauritania national football team]] on several occasions, most recently in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]] |author=Courtney, Barrie |title=International Matches 2000 - Africa |url=http://www.rsssf.com/intldetails/2000af.html |date=2 February 2005 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121017035644/http://www.rsssf.com/intldetails/2000af.html |archivedate=2012-10-17 |df= }}</ref>

