'''Mario Todman''' (born 29 November 1974 in [[Road Town]], [[Tortola]]) is a [[sprint (running)|sprinter]] who represented the [[British Virgin Islands]].
Todman represented [[British Virgin Islands]] at the [[Summer Olympics]] when he competed in the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta]], he entered the [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|4x100 metres relay]] and the [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 400 metres relay|4x400 metres relay]] the team finished 7th and 6th in there heats respectively so didn't qualify for the next round.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/to/mario-todman-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>
His olderr brother [[Willis Todman|Willis]] also competed at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in the relays.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/to/mario-todman-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>
