{{unreferenced|date=December 2006}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Oulun Energia Areena | nickname = Oulu Ice Hall | former_names = Raksilan jäähalli | image = OulunEnergiaAreena.jpg | caption = | fullname = | location = [[Oulu]], [[Finland]] | opened = 1975 | renovated = | expanded = | owner = | operator = | capacity = 6,614 | tenants = [[Kärpät]] (ice hockey) | website = }} '''Oulun Energia Areena''' or '''Oulu Ice Hall''' ({{lang-fi|Oulun jäähalli}}) is an arena in the [[Raksila]] district of [[Oulu]], in [[Finland]]. It is primarily used for [[ice hockey]], and is the home arena of [[Kärpät]]. It opened in 1975 and holds 6,614 people. The arena's former name was ''Raksilan jäähalli''. The name was changed to Oulun Energia Areena in 2006, after a sponsorship deal with [[Oulun Energia]], an energy company based in [[Oulu]].
