{{Infobox country at games | NOC = PHI | NOCname = [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] | oldcode = | year = 1994 | date = | games = Asian Games | location = [[Hiroshima]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | officials = | gold = 3 | silver = 2 | bronze = 8 | rank = 14 | appearances = auto | seealso = | website = {{URL|www.olympic.ph}}&nbsp;{{en icon}} }}
The '''[[Philippines]]''' participated in the [[1994 Asian Games]] held in [[Hiroshima]], [[Japan]] from October 2 to October 16, 1994. Ranked 14th with 3 gold medals, 2 silver medals and 8 bronze medals with a total of 13 over-all medals.
The Filipinos' triple gold all came in Boxing where Mansueto Velasco, Jr. reigned supreme in the light-flyweight division, Elias Recaido Jr. in the flyweight class, and Reynaldo Galido in the light-welterweight category. The three-two-eight gold-silver-bronze showing turned out to be the seventh best by the country at that time in the 43-year history and 12 Asiad stagings.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=JqMxAAAAIBAJ&sjid=2QoEAAAAIBAJ&pg=4868%2C3236208 RP boxers get big heroes' welcome], Manila Standard</ref>
